<!-- Executive Summary Section -->

<h2 id="introduction">A. Introduction:</h2>
<p>
  This report presents the findings of an ASHRAE Level II Energy Audit, Water Audit, and Retro-commissioning (RCx) study
  conducted at
  <strong>{{project.property_address}}</strong>. The analysis identified potential annual savings of
  <strong>{{formatCurrency potentialSavings}}</strong> through the implementation of energy and water efficiency
  measures.
  The property currently has an annual energy consumption of <strong>{{formatNumber
    totalUsage.totalEnergyUsage}}</strong> kWh
  and water consumption of <strong>{{formatNumber totalUsage.waterUsage}}</strong> gallons.
  The recommended measures include
  {{#if recommendations.length}}
  {{#each recommendations}}
  {{#if @last}}and {{/if}}{{this.title}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}
  {{/each}}
  {{else}}
  lighting upgrades, HVAC optimization, and water conservation measures
  {{/if}}.
</p>

<p>
  At the request of <strong>{{project.company_name}}</strong>, Vert Energy Group (VEG) performed ASHRAE Level II Energy
  Audit,
  Water Audit and a retro-commissioning (RCx) study of the base building systems at
  <strong>{{project.property_address}}</strong>.
  Built in <strong>{{project.property_year_built}}</strong>, this <strong>{{project.building_type}}</strong> building is
  comprised of
  <strong>{{project.description}}</strong>. The <strong>{{project.building_type}}</strong> portion of this property has
  a gross floor area of
  <strong>{{formatNumber project.property_gross_floor_area}}</strong> ft².
</p>

<p>
  The study is referred to as The Existing Buildings Energy and Water Efficiency (EBEWE) Program, was established by Los
  Angeles Municipal Code (LAMC)
  Division 97, Article 1, Chapter IX with the purpose of reducing energy and water consumption by building in the City
  of Los Angeles.
  The efficiency improvements (if implemented) will lower the use of energy, water, and greenhouse gas emissions
  citywide.
</p>

